      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Is it a problem that *something* uses `boost::filesystem`? Does it conflicts with our own (non-use), or is it a lot of extra code to build? At least it could be specifically gated for the windows build.\r\n\r\nIn the longer run `boost::process` could be replaced with another library, or some own solution. It doesn't seem like rocket science though it is tricky to get right in a cross-platform way (especially windows, I guess :smile:)",
